<doc id="824895" wikidata="Q504463" url="?curid=824895" title="Jan Svěrák">
<text>Jan Svěrák () (born 6 February 1965 in Žatec) is a Czech film director. He is the son of screenwriter and actor Zdeněk Svěrák. He studied documentary filmmaking at the FAMU. He and his films have received awards including the Academy Award, Crystal Globe, Golden Globe Award, and Tokyo Grand Prix.

He lives in Prague.

== Work ==
His mockumentary debut Ropáci (Oilgobblers) won student Academy Award for Best Student Film. His most famous film Kolya was one of three Czech feature films winning Oscar.

